title: Transcription profiling to ompare the effects of Vitamin D3 treatment of mouse bone marrow derived dendritic cells with control, untreated cells, and additional effects of maturation of either treated or control cells with LPS

attributes.name: Title
attributes.value: Transcription profiling to ompare the effects of Vitamin D3 treatment of mouse bone marrow derived dendritic cells with control, untreated cells, and additional effects of maturation of either treated or control cells with LPS

attributes.name: Description
attributes.value: This experiment is designed to compare the effects of Vitamin D3 treatment of mouse bone marrow derived dendritic cells with control, untreated cells, and additional effects of maturation of either treated or control cells with LPS.

attributes.name: Description
attributes.value: Bone marrow cells from CBA/Ca or C57BL/10 mice were cultured in RPMI 1640 (Gibco BRL, UK) plus 10% v/v FCS, 50mg/ml Penicillin-Streptomycin, 2mM L-glutamine and 50mM 2-mercaptoethanol (R10 medium) supplemented with approximately 5ng/ml GM-CSF (harvested from supernatant of X63.10 transfectants). On days 3 and 6, non-adherent cells were removed, the remaining cells being cultured in fresh medium supplemented with GM-CSF and harvested for use on day 7. Where indicated, vitamin D3 (1á, 25-dihydroxyvitamin D3) (Sigma, Gillingham, UK) was added to a final concentration of 10-7M on days 3 and 6. E. coli-derived lipopolysaccharide (Sigma, Gillingham, UK) was added to a final concentration of 1mg/ml on day 6 to stimulate maturation of the DC culture.

attributes.name: Description
attributes.value: Mean values for each reporter in each hybridization were generated by "fusing" the data within BlueFuse. Each hybridization was then corrected for channel "cross-talk" by applying Ch1=(Ch1-0.05*Ch2) and Ch2=(Ch2-0.05*Ch1).  Each channel dataset was then globally normalised such that the sum of all signals per channel = 500,000.  Geometric means were then calculated for values from the biological and dye swap replicates of each sample type across all hybridizations.

title: Transcription profiling of neuroblastoma tumors with and without MYCN amplification

attributes.name: Title
attributes.value: Transcription profiling of neuroblastoma tumors with and without MYCN amplification

attributes.name: Description
attributes.value: Purpose: Clinical courses of neuroblastomas (NBs) range from rapid progression with fatal outcome despite intensive multimodality therapies to spontaneous regression. Amplified MYCN oncogene defines a subgroup with poor outcome. However, a substantial number of MYCN single-copy NBs exhibits an aggressive phenotype similar to that of MYCN-amplified NBs even in the absence of high MYCN mRNA and/or protein levels. Experimental Design: To identify shared molecular mechanisms that mediate the aggressive phenotype in MYCN amplified and single-copy high-risk NBs, we defined genetic programs evoked by ectopically expressed MYCN in vitro and analyzed them in high-risk versus low-risk NB tumors (n=49) using cDNA microarrays. Candidate gene and protein expression was validated in a separate cohort of 117 patients using quantitative PCR (QPCR) and in a panel of NB tumors using immunohistochemistry. Results: We identified a genetic signature characterized by Skp2, encoding the F-box protein of the SCFSkp2 E3-ligase, and a subset of MYCN and of E2F targets to be highly expressed in high-risk NBs. We validated the findings for Skp2 and analyzed its expression in relation to MYCN and E2F-1 expression in a separate cohort (n=117) using QPCR. Most importantly, high Skp2 expression proved to be a highly significant marker of dire prognosis independent of both MYCN status and disease stage, on the basis of multivariate analysis of event-free survival (hazard ratio, 3.54

attributes.name: Description
attributes.value:
1 Sample Treatment Protocol

All neuroblastoma samples of this set were obtained prior to any cytotoxic treatment and were snap-frozen immediately after surgery.
Prior to RNA extraction tumor cell content was checked by a pathologist and only samples with >60% tumor content were processed further.

attributes.name: Description

1 RNA Extraction

Total RNA was extracted according to the published protocols(1). We used an Agilent BioAnalyzer 2100 (Agilent, Palo Alto, CA) to assess the integrity of total RNA from tumors.

1. Wie J. S., Khan J. Purification of total RNA from mammalian cells and tissues. In: D. Bowtell, J Sambrock, editors. DNA microarrays: a molecular cloning manual. Cold Spring Harbor, New York: Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory Press: 2002. P.110-9

1 RT Reaction:\\
After TRIzole purification and RNeasy, RNA is re-suspended in H2O. Take 1 ul for RNA concentration measurement, and make sure the total amount of RNA for labeling is more than 15 ug, usually 20 ug. For amplified RNA, use 2 ug amplified RNA per labeling per slide.\\

Concentrate RNA to 23.2 ul with Microcon-30.\\

5X First Strand Buffer|8 ul

1 Labeling Reaction:\\

1.To each labeling reaction, add 5 ul of 500 mM EDTA (pH 8.0), mix well before adding NaOH\\
2.Add 10 ul 1 M NaOH, mix well\\
3.65 C for 20 minutes to hydrolyze RNA, then cool to R/T \\
4.Add 10 ul 1 M HCl to neutralize NaOH \\
5.Probe purification with Qiagen PCR spin column protocol.\\
a.Add 350 ul PB buffer to RT reaction and transfer QIAquick column.\\
b.Spin at maximum speed for 1 minute.\\
c.Wash with 750 ul phosphate wash buffer (5 mM KPO4, pH 8.0 + 80 percent EtOH - use this home-made buffer to avoid Tris).\\
d.Spin at maximum speed for 1 minute.\\
e.Repeat wash steps c and d.\\
f.Empty collection tube and spin at maximum speed for 1 minute.\\
g.Transfer column to fresh tube, Elute with 30 ul elution buffer (4 mM KPO4, pH 8.5) with 1 minute incubation followed by spin at maximum speed for 1 minute.\\
h.Repeat elution step g.\\
i.Speedvac dry (approx. 40 minutes)\\
6.Cy Dye coupling \\
a.Re-suspend the cDNA in 4.5 ul 0.1 M carbonate buffer, pH 9.0 (freshly made, every two weeks, store at room temperature)\\
b.Add 4.5 ul NHS-Cy dyes (re-suspended in DMSO. AVOID ANY MOISTURE!!)\\
c.Incubate the reactions in dark for 1 hour in room temperature.\\

1 RT Purification:\\

1.Add 35 ul 100 mM NaOAc pH 5.2 to the reaction.\\
2.Add 250 ul PB buffer and follow QIAquick PCR purification protocol.\\
3.Elute 2X in 30 ul H2O.\\
At this step, 1 ul of sample can be taken for dye incorporation and analysis using NanoDrop Cy3/Cy5 program.\\
4.Mix the probes of Cy3 and Cy5 in equal amount. Speedvac dry (approx. 40 minutes).\\

1 Pre-hybridization:\\
1.Prepare pre -hybridization buffer (5xSSC, 0.1 percent SDS and 1 percent bovine serum albumin, BSA Sigma Cat#A-9418)\\
2.Place slides to be analyzed into a staining dish, fill with pre-hybridization buffer, and incubate at 42 C for 45 minutes.\\
3.Wash the slides in a Wheaton slide rack at room temperature with DIH2O with agitation for 2 min.\\
4.Dip the slides in room temperature isopropanol and dry by centrifugation at 700 rpm for 5 min. Inspect slides to make sure there is no protein marks on the slides. If there is, repeat step 3 and 4.\\

Slides should be used immediately following pre-hybridization, at least within one hour.\\

1 Hybridization:\\

1.Re-dissolve the combined probes in 27 ul 1X hybridization solution (240 ul H2O, 250 ul 20XSSC, 10 ul 10 percent SDS, 500 ul Formamide = 1ml) and combine with COT1-DNA and Poly(A)-DNA to block nonspecific hybridization\\
{table}
|
Cy5/Cy3 labeled probes | 27 ul
Poly dA (8 mg/ml)| 1.3 ul
Yeast tRNA (4 mg/ml) | 1.3 ul
CoT-1 DNA (10 mg/ml, concentrated) | 1.3 ul

Total |30.9 ul
{table}

2.Denature at 95 C for 2 minutes\\
3.Apply 14 ul 5X SSC onto each modified hybridization chamber to prevent drying.\\
4.Apply probes to the cover slide that is big enough for the printed area (e.g. 60 mm cover slip for 22K array).Then put the pre-hybridization microarray slide on the top of the cover slip, invert, and hybridize in a humidified chamber at 42 C for 16-24 hours.\\

1 Wash:\\

Place slide into a staining dish with Wash#1 at R/T until cover slip falls off.\\
{table}

Wash#3: | 4 minutes at R/T in 0.06 X SSC
{table}


Spin immediately (700 rpm for 5 minutes at R/T) \\
